>> source: https://www.aspicyperspective.com/best-ranchero-sauce-recipe/
>> serves: 3 cups
>> total time: 17 minutes

Place a #saute pan{} over medium heat and add the @olive oil {1%Tbsp}and @shallots{2}. Sauté the shallots for ~{2%minutes}. Then add the @garlic{2%cloves} and sauté another 1 to ~{2%minutes}.

Drain the @piquillo peppers{12%oz} or @roasted red peppers (alternative){1%jar}. Add the @chopped green chiles{4.5%oz}, @vegetable stock{1%cup}, @cumin{1%Tbsp}, @brown sugar{1%Tbsp}, and @liquid smoke{1/4%tsp} to the saute pan, except for the heavy cream. Simmer the ranchero sauce for ~{10%minutes}. Remove from heat.

Using an #immersion blender{}, puree the ranchero sauce until smooth. Then stir in the @heavy cream{1/2%cup}. @Salt{} to taste.
